0550-fifa-to-take-legal-action-against-beoutq-over-world-cup-broadcasts |archive-date=26 August 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"lJrJH\">{{Cite news |last=Draper |first=Kevin |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/11/sports/soccer/world-cup-soccer.html |title=Fox and Others Will Feel Pain of U.S. Absence at World Cup |date=11 October 2017 |work=The New York Times |access-date=26 October 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024072730/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/11/sports/soccer/world-cup-soccer.html |archive-date=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Oo1hn\">{{Cite news |last=Deitsch |first=Richard |url=https://www.si.com/tech-media/2017/10/11/usa-world-cup-elimination-fox-sports-coverage-mexico-el-tri |title=With USMNT eliminated from World Cup, Fox must refocus coverage plan |date=11 October 2017 |work=Sports Illustrated |access-date=26 October 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026111153/https://www.si.com/tech-media/2017/10/11/usa-world-cup-elimination-fox-sports-coverage-mexico-el-tri |archive-date=26 October 2017}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"1M4WS\">{{Cite news |last=Shaw |first=Lucas |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-10-11/fox-is-said-to-project-20-million-in-lost-world-cup-ad-sales |title=Fox projects up to $20&nbsp;million in lost World Cup ad sales |date=11 October 2017 |access-date=26 October 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026111201/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-10-11/fox-is-said-to-project-20-million-in-lost-world-cup-ad-sales |archive-date=26 October 2017 |publisher=Bloomberg |last2=Novy-Williams |first2=Eben |last3=Broudway |first3=Ira}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"wx1ZL\">{{Cite news |last=Steinberg |first=Brian |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/world-cup-ratings-fox-telemundo-tv-viewership-1202864539/ |title=World Cup Strains to Reverse Sports-Viewing Trends |date=3 July 2018 |work=Variety |access-date=14 October 2018 |url-status=live |arch