150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-11-6-2018.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 11.6.2018|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=November 7, 2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=November 7, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The club has reason to celebrate, but big changes leave the future uncertain.\n |LineColor       = 97363B\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nThe first season was met with a mixed to positive response from critics. On the review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the first season holds a 72% approval rating with an average rating of 6.43 out of 10 based on 36 reviews. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Mayans M.C.'' is a thrilling drama with compelling characters, but it struggles to find its pace and the Tellers are hard to forget.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/mayans_mc/s01|title=Mayans MC: Season 1|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]]|accessdate= April 4, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the season has a score of 57 out of 100, based on 19 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/mayans-mc|title=Mayans MC: Season 1|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive|CBS Interactive Inc.]]|accessdate=December 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| noshare  = y\n| title1   = [[#ep1|Perro/Oc]]\n| date1    = September 4, 2018\n| rs1      = 1.1\n| viewers1 = 2.53<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1     = 1.0\n| dvrv1    = 2.51\n| total1   = 2.1\n| totalv1  = 5.05<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/dvr-ratings/cable-live-7-ratings-sept-3-9-2018/|title='Mayans M.C.' premiere leads, 'It's Always Sunny' does well in cable Live +7 ratings for Sept. 3-9|last=Welch|first=Alex|date=September 24, 2018|work=TV by the Numbers|accessdate=September 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n| title2   = [[#ep2|Escorpi\u00f3n/Dzec]]\n| date2    